# Weekly Curriculum Breakdown
## Machine Learning and Intelligence Course - Spring 2025

---

## Week 1: Introduction to Machine Learning & Environment Setup

### Learning Objectives
- Understand what machine learning is and its applications
- Set up the 2025ml conda environment
- Explore the course bot and its capabilities
- Understand the final project goals

### Topics Covered
- **ML Fundamentals**: What is ML, types of learning, applications in policy studies
- **Course Overview**: Structure, expectations, AI assistant features
- **Environment Setup**: 2025ml conda environment, essential libraries
- **Final Project Preview**: mynavi.jp job classifier introduction

### Activities
- **Lecture**: ML introduction and course orientation
- **Lab**: Environment setup and verification
- **AI Interaction**: First conversation with course bot
- **Exercise**: Simple ML example with provided skeleton code

### Deliverables
- [ ] 2025ml environment setup verification
- [ ] Course bot interaction log (3 meaningful conversations)
- [ ] Basic ML concept quiz via AI assistant

### Skeleton Code Provided
- `week1_environment_setup.py` - Environment verification script
- `week1_ml_intro.py` - Basic ML example with fill-in-the-blanks

---

## Week 2: Python for Data Science

### Learning Objectives
- Master essential Python libraries for ML
- Understand data structures and manipulation
- Practice with pandas and numpy
- Learn basic visualization techniques

### Topics Covered
- **Python Review**: Essential syntax and data structures
- **NumPy**: Arrays, operations, mathematical functions
- **Pandas**: DataFrames, data manipulation, file I/O
- **Matplotlib/Seaborn**: Basic visualization techniques

### Activities
- **Lecture**: Python fundamentals for data science
- **Lab**: Data manipulation exercises with skeleton code
- **Exercise**: Create visualizations from sample datasets
- **AI Tutoring**: Interactive Python concept review

### Deliverables
- [ ] Data manipulation exercises (5/5 completed)
- [ ] Visualization assignment (3 charts created)
- [ ] Python fundamentals quiz via AI assistant

### Skeleton Code Provided
- `week2_data_manipulation.py` - Pandas exercises skeleton
- `week2_visualization.py` - Plotting exercises skeleton

---

## Week 3: Data Collection & Web Scraping

### Learning Objectives
- Understand web scraping principles and ethics
- Learn to use requests and BeautifulSoup
- Practice scraping mynavi.jp company data
- Understand data storage and organization

### Topics Covered
- **Web Scraping Ethics**: Responsible scraping practices
- **HTTP Requests**: Using requests library
- **HTML Parsing**: BeautifulSoup for data extraction
- **Data Storage**: CSV, JSON formats
- **Rate Limiting**: Respectful scraping practices

### Activities
- **Lecture**: Web scraping fundamentals and ethics
- **Lab**: Scraping exercises with skeleton code
- **Exercise**: Build mynavi.jp scraper skeleton
- **AI Assistance**: Debugging scraping code

### Deliverables
- [ ] Basic web scraper implementation
- [ ] mynavi.jp scraper skeleton (partially functional)
- [ ] Scraping ethics reflection (300 words)
- [ ] Web scraping quiz via AI assistant

### Skeleton Code Provided
- `week3_basic_scraper.py` - General scraping skeleton
- `week3_mynavi_scraper.py` - mynavi.jp specific skeleton
- `week3_data_parser.py` - HTML parsing skeleton

---

## Week 4: Data Preprocessing & Exploratory Data Analysis

### Learning Objectives
- Master data cleaning techniques
- Perform comprehensive exploratory data analysis
- Handle missing data and outliers
- Prepare data for machine learning

### Topics Covered
- **Data Cleaning**: Missing values, duplicates, outliers
- **Data Transformation**: Normalization, scaling, encoding
- **EDA Techniques**: Statistical summaries, visualizations
- **Data Quality**: Assessment and improvement strategies

### Activities
- **Lecture**: Data preprocessing theory and best practices
- **Lab**: EDA exercises with real datasets
- **Exercise**: Clean and analyze scraped mynavi.jp data
- **AI Tutoring**: EDA technique guidance

### Deliverables
- [ ] Data cleaning pipeline implementation
- [ ] EDA report with visualizations (5+ charts)
- [ ] Data quality assessment document
- [ ] EDA quiz via AI assistant

### Skeleton Code Provided
- `week4_data_cleaning.py` - Data cleaning skeleton
- `week4_eda.py` - Exploratory analysis skeleton
- `week4_preprocessing.py` - Preprocessing pipeline skeleton

---

## Week 5: Supervised Learning - Classification

### Learning Objectives
- Understand classification algorithms
- Implement basic classification models
- Evaluate model performance
- Compare different algorithms

### Topics Covered
- **Classification Theory**: Logistic regression, decision trees, SVM
- **Model Training**: Training/validation split, cross-validation
- **Evaluation Metrics**: Accuracy, precision, recall, F1-score
- **Model Comparison**: Algorithm selection criteria

### Activities
- **Lecture**: Classification algorithms and theory
- **Lab**: Implement classification models with skeleton code
- **Exercise**: Classify sample datasets
- **AI Assessment**: Interactive classification quiz

### Deliverables
- [ ] Classification model implementations (3 algorithms)
- [ ] Model performance comparison report
- [ ] Classification concepts quiz via AI assistant

### Skeleton Code Provided
- `week5_logistic_regression.py` - Logistic regression skeleton
- `week5_decision_trees.py` - Decision tree skeleton
- `week5_svm.py` - Support vector machine skeleton
- `week5_model_evaluation.py` - Evaluation metrics skeleton

---

## Week 6: Text Mining & Feature Extraction

### Learning Objectives
- Understand text preprocessing techniques
- Extract features from text data
- Apply text mining to company descriptions
- Prepare text data for classification

### Topics Covered
- **Text Preprocessing**: Tokenization, stemming, lemmatization
- **Feature Extraction**: Bag of words, TF-IDF, n-grams
- **Text Vectorization**: Converting text to numerical features
- **Japanese Text Processing**: Special considerations for Japanese

### Activities
- **Lecture**: Text mining fundamentals
- **Lab**: Text preprocessing exercises
- **Exercise**: Extract features from mynavi.jp company descriptions
- **AI Tutoring**: Text mining technique guidance

### Deliverables
- [ ] Text preprocessing pipeline
- [ ] Feature extraction implementation
- [ ] Text analysis report on company descriptions
- [ ] Text mining quiz via AI assistant

### Skeleton Code Provided
- `week6_text_preprocessing.py` - Text cleaning skeleton
- `week6_feature_extraction.py` - Feature extraction skeleton
- `week6_japanese_processing.py` - Japanese text handling skeleton

---

## Week 7: Model Evaluation & Selection

### Learning Objectives
- Master model evaluation techniques
- Understand overfitting and underfitting
- Implement cross-validation
- Select optimal models

### Topics Covered
- **Model Evaluation**: Cross-validation, holdout validation
- **Performance Metrics**: Comprehensive evaluation techniques
- **Overfitting/Underfitting**: Bias-variance tradeoff
- **Model Selection**: Algorithm comparison and selection

### Activities
- **Lecture**: Model evaluation theory
- **Lab**: Evaluation exercises with skeleton code
- **Exercise**: Evaluate and compare text classification models
- **AI Assessment**: Model evaluation quiz

### Deliverables
- [ ] Cross-validation implementation
- [ ] Model evaluation report
- [ ] Best model selection with justification
- [ ] Evaluation concepts quiz via AI assistant

### Skeleton Code Provided
- `week7_cross_validation.py` - CV implementation skeleton
- `week7_model_evaluation.py` - Evaluation metrics skeleton
- `week7_model_selection.py` - Model comparison skeleton

---

## Week 8: Advanced Classification Techniques

### Learning Objectives
- Learn ensemble methods
- Implement advanced classifiers
- Optimize model performance
- Apply techniques to text classification

### Topics Covered
- **Ensemble Methods**: Random forests, gradient boosting
- **Hyperparameter Tuning**: Grid search, random search
- **Advanced Algorithms**: XGBoost, LightGBM
- **Performance Optimization**: Feature selection, dimensionality reduction

### Activities
- **Lecture**: Advanced classification techniques
- **Lab**: Ensemble method implementation
- **Exercise**: Optimize mynavi.jp classifier performance
- **AI Tutoring**: Advanced technique guidance

### Deliverables
- [ ] Ensemble model implementation
- [ ] Hyperparameter optimization results
- [ ] Performance improvement report
- [ ] Advanced techniques quiz via AI assistant

### Skeleton Code Provided
- `week8_ensemble_methods.py` - Random forest skeleton
- `week8_hyperparameter_tuning.py` - Optimization skeleton
- `week8_advanced_classifiers.py` - Advanced algorithms skeleton

